    "description": "Mahindra Finance Advisory Limited is actively seeking a talented and motivated Investment Banker to join our dynamic team in Nashik. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Mahindra Finance Advisory Limited:\nMahindra Finance Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Nashik, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Mahindra Finance Advisory Limited!",
